 - Eighty-fourth task (the LAST S7 task) of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program. Polishes the professional information for clarity WITHOUT replacing the design. (1) Evidence vs inference: the item page rendered the 原文 (source/evidence) link and the generated 讲义 (lesson) sections with no marker, so a reader could mistake the auto-generated inference for the original; a const PROVENANCE_NOTE (a 讲义·推断 badge + a sentence saying the lesson is an auto-generated inference summary from the 原文, not the original) is now prepended in the CENTRAL lessonHTML(lesson) helper, so every lesson render (today/item/reveal/review) is labelled as inference, and the todayPage inline lesson render was refactored to call lessonHTML (DRY + the marker; output otherwise identical -- same section numbering + escaping). (2) Accessibility: the reveal button now carries aria-controls and, on click, moves focus INTO the revealed box (tabindex=-1) -- proper disclosure semantics; every interactive handler was already on a native focusable button/link with an accessible name, buttons are 44px (touch), and :focus-visible exists (T080). (3) Reduced-motion: verified the existing prefers-reduced-motion rule disables all animation/transition but RESTORES the animated content classes (.fr, .bw, both opacity:0 in HERO_CSS) to opacity:1, and the gauge/hero-video jump to their final state in JS -- so no content/function is lost (only the decorative .fx-cosmos meteor stays hidden). The polish lives entirely in page-body functions, so the six-theme visual/motion contract is BYTE-IDENTICAL; BUILD recomputed via its self-hash (d1dfcb3b7447 -> 452f7c5de919). release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED (live still serves b189d3cc0703). New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/a11y_content_audit.py. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S7-P04-T084/: browser_measurements.json (the 推断 marker renders, the reveal moves focus into the box, the grade buttons are keyboard-focusable, the reduced-motion CSSOM rule restores .fr/.bw), a11y_harness.html, pre_fix_worker.js, known_gaps.md (discloses the honest scoping -- the title's Diff view is the S5-T062 version-diff, not redone here -- and the reduced-motion/screen-reader test form) and adversarial_review.md. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S7-P04-T084/test-results/a11y_content_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): key tasks are keyboard/touch operable (native named buttons + focus moves into revealed content), evidence (原文 link) vs inference (讲义·推断 marker) is clearly distinguished (the pre-fix worker had no marker -- the check is discriminating), reduced-motion disables animation but restores the .fr/.bw content (removing the restore fails the check -- it is load-bearing), and the six-theme contract is byte-identical. Realtime not regressed (NOT deployed; live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production 0 (NOT_DEPLOYED); 1 read-only GET, 1 in-app-browser render. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
